Use Timeshift to backup and restore system files and settings, whereas user files are not touched
https://github.com/teejee2008/timeshift

In Ubuntu 16, select include hidden files to have user settings (e.g. bashrc) in the backup file
In Ubuntu 14, user settings and files (e.g. bashrc, Desktop, Documents), do not put any folders

Can restore with LiveCD by installing Timeshift into the LiveCD system
